odies within the belt\nalone cannot reproduce the two populations observed. This argues for an\nalternative or additional scenario, such as planetesimals being born with high\ninclinations, or the presence of a `$\\beta$ Pic c' planet, potentially\nmigrating outwards near the belt's inner edge.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 11 Feb 2019 19:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-20"}
