tent with the available s-process nucleosynthesis\nmodels for solar metallicity massive AGB stars, which predict overproduction of\n46Ca relatively to the other Ca isotope and the creation of the radiactive\nisotope 41Ca but no change in the total Ca abundance. A minority of the stars\nseem to show a significant Ca depletion (by up to 1.0 dex). Possible\nexplanations are offered to explain their apparent and unexpected Ca depletion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Feb 2019 10:06:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-27"}
