{"id":"1902.04388","submitter":"David Ho","authors":"Oliver Gould, David L.-J. Ho, Arttu Rajantie","title":"Towards Schwinger production of magnetic monopoles in heavy-ion\n  collisions","comments":null,"journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. D 100, 015041 (2019)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevD.100.015041","report-no":"IMPERIAL-TP-2019-DH-01; HIP-2019-2/TH","categories":"hep-th hep-ph","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Magnetic monopoles may be produced by the Schwinger effect in the strong\nmagnetic fields of peripheral heavy-ion collisions. We review the form of the\nelectromagnetic fields in such collisions and calculate from first principles\nthe cross section for monopole pair production. Using the worldline instanton\nmethod, we work to all orders in the magnetic charge, and hence are not\nhampered by the breakdown of perturbation theory. Our result depends on the\nspacetime inhomogeneity through a single dimensionless parameter, the Keldysh\nparameter, which is independent of collision energy for a given monopole mass.\nFor realistic heavy-ion collisions, the computational cost of the calculation\nbecomes prohibitive and the finite size of the monopoles needs to be taken into\naccount, and therefore our current results are not applicable to them.\nNonetheless, our results show that the spacetime dependence enhances the\nproduction cross section and would therefore lead to stronger monopole mass\nbounds than in the constant-field case.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 12 Feb 2019 13:56:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-07"}
